The paper focuses on developing a deep saliency model using eye-tracking data and image transformations. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper utilizes deep learning techniques and analyzes human attention, which suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it studies how humans interact with images. Finally, the paper introduces a new saliency dataset, which could also place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
